ASABA – A total of 825 delegates have been accredited to vote in the Governorship primary elections of the People’s Democratic Party ( PDP) currently holding at the Stephen Keshi Stadium, Asaba. The total of accredited delegates for the 25 local government areas of the state were Aniocha- North 28 Aniocha South- 34, Oshimili South- 34, Oshimili North-31, Ika North East- 43, Ika South – 37, Ndokwa East – 31, Ndokwa West- 30, Ethiope- East -33, Ethiope West -33, Okpe- 31, Sapele- 34, Ughelli North- 34, Ughelli South- 33, Isoko North- 40, Isoko South- 34, Warri South- 37, Warri North-31, Warri South- West-31, Udu – 31, Uvwie- 31, Burutu- 32, Patani- 30, Bomadi- 31, Ukwuani- 31. -Advertisement- Meanwhile, a total of 299 delegates were accredited for Delta North Senatorial District while a total of 260 and 266 were accredited for Delta Central and Delta South respectively. Earlier, Resident Electoral Commissioner of Delta State, Mr Monday Udoh-Tom lauded the party for the peaceful conduct of the House of Assembly and House of Representatives Primary as he called for the same in the Governorship election for the good of the state. However, agents to the Senator James Manager Tarabiri Government noted that Delegates should not be allowed to write their names behind the ballot papers after casting their votes. Also, agent to Deputy Governor, Barr. Kingsley Otuaro, Mr Arex Akemetubo equally advised the delegates should not be allowed to take a picture of the ballow after casting their votes.